cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper deals with convolutional neural networks and their application to image processing, specifically on spherical data. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of meshes and geodesic grids, which falls under the category of computer graphics (cs.GR). The paper proposes a new method for convolutional neural networks, which could be of interest to researchers in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of data discretization, which is relevant to researchers in neural networks (cs.NE).
